'''Noa Noëll Lang''' (born 17 June 1999) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left winger]] or [[left midfielder]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]], on loan from [[Serie A]] club [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]], and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Club career==
===Ajax===
On 1 December 2019, Lang became the first [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] player to score a hat-trick on his first [[Eredivisie|league]] start in 60 years as Ajax came from two goals down to beat [[FC Twente|Twente]] 5–2.<ref>{{cite web |title=FC Twente 2-5 Ajax: Lang hits hat-trick on league debut as leaders fight back |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50623088 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=3 December 2019 |date=1 December 2019}}</ref> Later that month, Lang scored his first goal in the [[KNVB Cup]] for Ajax, netting the opening goal in a 4–3 away win over [[SC Telstar|Telstar]] in the [[2019–20 KNVB Cup#Second round|second round]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/12/18/netherlands/knvb-beker/stormvogels-telstar-combinatie/afc-ajax/3182607/|title=Telstar 3–4 Ajax|website=Soccerway|date=18 December 2019}}</ref>

In January 2020, following Ajax's signing of [[Ryan Babel]] in Lang's position, he was loaned out to fellow Eredivisie side Twente for the remainder of the [[2019–20 Eredivisie|season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaboutajax.com/2020/01/official-noa-lang-joins-fc-twente-on-loan-for-the-rest-of-the-season/|title=Official: Noa Lang joins FC Twente on loan for the rest of the season|website=All About Ajax|date=18 January 2020|accessdate=14 March 2021}}</ref>

===Club Brugge===
====2020–21 season: Loan and league title====
On 5 October 2020, Ajax and [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] reached a transfer agreement for Lang to move to Brugge on an initial loan with an obligation to make the signing permanent by 1 July 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|date=5 October 2020|title=Noa Lang goes to Club Brugge, Bandé returns to Ajax|url=https://english.ajax.nl/archive/noa-lang-goes-to-club-brugge-bande-returns-to-ajax/|access-date=12 March 2021|website=english.ajax.nl|language=}}</ref> Three weeks later, he scored his first goal for the club from the penalty-spot in a losing effort against [[Oud-Heverlee Leuven|OH Leuven]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.proleague.be/nl/jpl/match/7ub54h3pv4doevrve15gtvmui|title=OH Leuven 2-1 Club Brugge|website=Pro League|date=24 October 2020|accessdate=14 March 2021|language=Dutch}}</ref> Lang scored in Club Brugge's 3–0 victory over [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in their penultimate [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] group stage match on 2 December to keep alive Club Brugge's hopes of qualifying for the knock-out round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029440/|title=Club Brugge 3-0 Zenit|website=UEFA|date=2 December 2020|accessdate=14 March 2021}}</ref> However, Club Brugge could only manage a 2–2 draw in the final match against [[Serie A|Italian]] side [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] and were parachuted down to the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] for the Round of 32.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/163196/lazio-2-2-brugge-aquile-squeak-through|title=Lazio 2-2 Brugge: Aquile squeak through|website=Football Italia|date=December 2020|accessdate=14 March 2021}}</ref>

On 28 January 2021, in his first appearance in a [[Bruges derby]] against [[Cercle Brugge KSV|Cercle]], Lang scored the winning goal as Club Brugge came back from 1–0 down to win 1–2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.proleague.be/nl/jpl/match/8a8emfhxadccxtyca9rsv8pka|title=Cercle Brugge 1-2 Club Brugge|website=Pro League|date=28 January 2021|accessdate=14 March 2021|language=Dutch}}</ref>

On 20 May, Lang scored as Brugge drew 3–3 with [[R.S.C. Anderlecht–Club Brugge KV rivalry|rivals]] [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] to win the [[2020–21 Belgian First Division A|Belgian First Division A]] title for the fourth time in six years and 17th time overall.<ref name=clinch>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/club-brugge-clinch-belgian-title-2021-05-20/|title=Club Brugge clinch Belgian title|website=Reuters|date=20 May 2021}}</ref> Lang was involved in 28 goal contributions during his first campaign with Club Brugge, scoring 17 goals and adding a further 11 assists.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leeds-live.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/brugge-lang-transfer-stance-leeds-20944876|title=Club Brugge double down on Noa Lang transfer stance as Leeds United-linked forward pictured|website=Leeds Live|date=1 July 2021|accessdate=17 July 2021}}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
On 17 July 2021, Lang scored in Club Brugge's 3–2 win over [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in the [[2021 Belgian Super Cup|Belgian Super Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/lang-nets-as-club-brugge-take-belgian-super-cup/|title=Lang nets as Club Brugge take Belgian super cup|website=Football Oranje|date=17 July 2021|accessdate=18 July 2021}}</ref> On 15 September, he earned the [[player of the match]] award in a 1–1 draw against [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) in the UEFA Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web|date=16 September 2021|title=Bruges-PSG: passé par Nantes, look à la Neymar… qui est Noa Lang, désigné homme du match|trans-title=Bruges-PSG: gone by Nantes, looking like Neymar, who is Noa Lang, designated man of the match|url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-des-champions/bruges-psg-passe-par-nantes-look-a-la-neymar-qui-est-noa-lang-designe-homme-du-match_AV-202109160162.html|access-date=16 September 2021|website=[[RMC (France)|RMC Sport]]|language=fr}}</ref>

=== PSV ===
On 8 July 2023, Dutch side [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] announced the signing of Lang on a five-year deal for a club record fee of €15 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=8 July 2023 |title=Oficial: Noa Lang é o reforço mais caro da história do PSV |trans-title=Official: Noa Lang is the most expensive reinforcement in PSV history |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/noticias/oficial-noa-lang-e-o-reforco-mais-caro-da-historia-do-psv-16661185.html |access-date=8 July 2023 |website= |publisher=[[O Jogo]] |language=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-08 |title=Transfer {{!}} PSV bolster attack with Dutch international Noa Lang |url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/transfer-psv-bolster-attack-with-dutch-international-noa-lang.htm |access-date=2023-07-08 |website=www.psv.nl |language=en-US |archive-date=15 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230715161546/https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/news/article/transfer-psv-bolster-attack-with-dutch-international-noa-lang.htm |url-status=dead }}</ref> In his first training session, he suffered an injury.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 July 2023 |title=Catastrophe en vue pour Noa Lang ? L'ancien joueur de Bruges s'est blessé lors de son premier entraînement avec le PSV (photo) |url=https://www.sudinfo.be/id685863/article/2023-07-10/catastrophe-en-vue-pour-noa-lang-lancien-joueur-de-bruges-sest-blesse-lors-de |access-date=10 July 2023 |website=Sudinfo |language=Fr}}</ref>  At first, the injury looked serious, but shortly after, Noa Lang was spotted training alone. His first game for the Dutch side was the [[2023 Johan Cruyff Shield]], which he decided by scoring the only goal.

===Napoli===
On 17 July 2025, Lang joined [[Serie A]] club [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]] on a five-year contract for a reported fee of €25 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 July 2025 |title=Napoli sign Dutch international forward Lang |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20250717-napoli-sign-dutch-international-forward-lang |access-date=18 July 2025 |website=France 24}}</ref> Later that year, on 22 November, he netted his first goal in a 3–1 win over [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/736900/atalanta-napoli |title=Napoli 3–1 Atalanta |publisher=ESPN |date=22 November 2025 }}</ref>

====Loan to Galatasaray====
On 23 January 2026, Lang signed on loan for [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] until the end of the [[2025–26 Galatasaray S.K. season|2025–26 season]], with a non-mandatory purchase option.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/gs-sportif-a-s/noa-lang-galatasarayda/59394|title=Noa Lang Galatasaray'da!|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=23 January 2026|access-date=23 January 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.galatasaray.org/haber/futbol/galatasaraya-hos-geldin-noa/59395|title=Galatasaray'a hoş geldin Noa!|publisher=Galatasaray S.K.|date=23 January 2026|access-date=23 January 2026}}</ref>

He made his debut for Galatasaray in a 4–0 [[Süper Lig]] win over [[Kayserispor]] on 1 February 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-mena/football/sper-lig/galatasaray-vs-kayserispor-2026-02-01#OverView|title=Galatasaray vs Kayserispor|access-date=18 February 2026|website=BeIN Sport}}</ref> His first goals for the club came in a 5–2 win over [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] on 17 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ad.nl/voetbal/noa-lang-zet-istanboel-in-vuur-en-vlam-met-twee-goals-tegen-juventus-deze-trainer-geeft-mij-wel-vertrouwen~a1226d04/?referrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F|title=Noa Lang zet Istanboel in vuur en vlam met twee goals tegen Juventus: ‘Deze trainer geeft mij wél vertrouwen’|date=18 February 2026|language=Dutch|website=AD}}</ref> A month later, on 18 March, he suffered a hand injury involving partial severing of his thumb as a result of a collision with an advertisement board during a Champions League match against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Salley |first=Emily |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c7vjvv119d0o |title=Lang's surgery for thumb injury 'went well' |publisher=BBC Sport |date=19 March 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Lang is of Surinamese descent through his biological father. He is a youth international for the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elfvoetbal.nl/buitenland/277897/zo-kan-het-nationaal-elftal-van-suriname-eruit-gaan-zien|title=Zo kan het nationaal elftal van Suriname eruit gaan zien|website=Elfvoetbal.nl}}</ref> Lang considers himself Dutch, [[Suriname]]se and [[Morocco|Moroccan]] but can't internationally represent the latter due to not having Moroccan citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|date=29 August 2020|title=Noa Lang lacht: 'Op mijn Instagram heb ik daar veel vragen over gehad'|url=https://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=376305|access-date=12 May 2021|website=Voetbalzone}}</ref>

Lang represented the Netherlands at youth level. He appeared at both the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/jeugd-mannen-onder-19/69757/definitieve-selectie-oranje-onder-19-voor-ek-georgië|title=DEFINITIEVE SELECTIE ORANJE ONDER 19 VOOR EK IN GEORGIË|language=Dutch|date=22 June 2017|access-date=18 February 2026|website=Ons Oranje}}</ref> and the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/jong-oranje/78721/ek-selectie-jong-oranje-brian-brobbey-debuteert|title=EK-SELECTIE JONG ORANJE: BRIAN BROBBEY DEBUTEERT|language=Dutch|date=15 March 2021|access-date=18 February 2026|website=Ons Oranje}}</ref>

On 8 October 2021, he made his debut for the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]] in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group G|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FIFA]]|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/qatar2022/qualifiers/uefa/match-center/400155686|title=Latvia v Netherlands game report|date=8 October 2021}}</ref> His first senior international goal came in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] fixture against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] on 14 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/jun/14/netherlands-wales-nations-league-match-report|title=Wales comeback thwarted by Memphis Depay’s last-gasp Netherlands winner|date=15 June 2022|access-date=18 February 2026|website=The Guardian}}</ref>

Lang was named in the final Netherlands squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/80525/van-gaal-maakt-26-koppige-wk-selectie-bekend |title=Van Gaal maakt 26-koppige WK-selectie bekend |trans-title=Van Gaal announces 26-man World Cup squad |publisher=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |date=11 November 2022 |access-date=12 November 2022 |language=nl}}</ref> His only appearance of the tournament came in the [[Battle of Lusail|quarter-final loss]] to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], where he appeared as an 113th-minute substitute for [[Cody Gakpo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/09/netherlands-v-argentina-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live-score-updates?page=with%3Ablock-63939ec88f08a6133634a857|title=Argentina into World Cup semi-final after beating Netherlands on penalties – as it happened|access-date=18 February 2026|date=10 December 2022|website=The Guardian}}</ref>

In June 2023, he represented the Netherlands at the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals]], scoring an equaliser in the sixth minute of stoppage time in the eventual 4–2 loss to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] at the semi-final stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65906729|title= Netherlands 2-4 Croatia: Zlatko Dalic's side seal Nations League final spot after extra-time thriller|date=14 June 2023|access-date=18 February 2026|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

Lang was not a member of the Dutch squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]] due to injury.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/40159196/netherlands-injured-de-jong-2024-euro-squad|title= Netherlands name injured De Jong in 2024 Euro squad|date=17 May 2024|access-date=18 February 2026|website=ESPN}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Lang was born in the Netherlands. His father is [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]], while his mother is Dutch.<ref>{{cite web |title=Arsenal transfer target Noa Lang has been investigated over anti-Semitic chant and refused to apologise |date=14 October 2021 |url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2021/10/14/noa-lang-arsenal-target-anti-semitism-history/ |access-date=15 November 2022}}</ref> His stepfather was Moroccan international footballer [[Nourdin Boukhari]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=369222|title=Noa Lang schiet in verdediging: 'Mensen denken: hij is een lichte jongen'|date=11 March 2020|publisher=voetbalzone.nl|language=Dutch}}</ref> During the spring season of 2025, whilst officiating a match, his father Jeffrey Lang was physically assaulted although he declined to press charges.<ref>{{Cite web | title='Cowardly act' - Netherlands star's dad knocked out at youth team match in shock footage {{!}} talkSPORT | url=https://talksport.com/football/3204279/netherlands-psv-noa-lang-father-knocked-out-eredivise/ | access-date=2025-09-01 | website=talksport.com}}</ref>

During the [[2009–10 in Turkish football|2009–10]] football season, Boukhari and Lang resided in [[Turkey]], playing for [[Kasımpaşa S.K.|Kasımpaşa]] and [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] junior team respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.kartalhaber.com/futbol-dunyasi-onu-konusuyor-noa-lang-besiktasli-cikti-45128.html|title=Futbol Dünyası Onu Konuşuyor... Noa Lang Beşiktaşlı Çıktı|publisher=kartalhaber.com|access-date=17 September 2017}}</ref>

== Controversy ==
In May 2021, a video circulated online showing Lang joining an [[Antisemitism|antisemitic]] chant of the Club Brugge supporters aimed at rival [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], who is seen as historically linked to the Jewish community.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/brugge-star-investigated-joining-anti-133847134.html|title=Brugge's Lang investigated for joining anti-Semitic chant|website=Yahoo|date=22 May 2021|accessdate=17 July 2021}}</ref> He was investigated by the [[Royal Belgian Football Association]]. While ignoring calls to apologize,<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.jpost.com/diaspora/antisemitism/belgian-soccer-star-defends-chanting-hed-rather-die-than-be-a-jew-669059 | title=Belgian soccer star defends chanting he'd 'rather die than be a Jew' | newspaper=The Jerusalem Post &#124; Jpost.com }}</ref> Lang justified his chantings with supporters as "a nickname" claiming that "racism and prejudice are well known to me [...] I didn’t want to offend anyone with that. I’m done with the subject and won’t be revisiting it." Lang, who played with Ajax, before joining Club Brugge, was defended by the team's organisation claiming that "there was no anti-Semitic undertone".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.voetbalzone.nl/doc.asp?uid=388710|title=Club Brugge komt met statement: 'Noa Lang was jarenlang speler bij Ajax|website=Voetbalzone|date=21 May 2021}}</ref> The Club Brugge fans have been noticed by the press for racist chants.<ref>"Racism Amongst Club Brugge Fans: Supporters from CB and RSC Anderlecht Give Their Opinion on What Happened During Sundays Match – 21bis." 21bis – Mediaplatform Voor Studenten, 21bis.be/2021/12/racism-amoungst-club-brugge-fans-supporters-from-cb-and-rsc-anderlecht-give-their-opinion-on-what-happened-during-sundays-match/.
</ref>

The [[Royal Belgian Football Association|RBFA]] condemned his behavior, the Belgian Foreign Minister [[Sophie Wilmès]] declared: "Unacceptable, unbearable and it has no place in our society. We must fight it as vigorously as all other forms of racism", political parties condemned the chant, while he was obliged by the [[Federal prosecutor's office (Belgium)|Federal prosecutor's office]] to visit the [[Kazerne Dossin Memorial, Museum and Documentation Centre|Kazerne Dossin Centre]] as a disciplinary measure.<ref>"Noa Lang Undergoes Punishment and Visits Former Deportation Camp." LFOTV.NET, 9 Sept. 2021, livefootballontv.net/noa-lang-undergoes-punishment-and-visits-former-deportation-camp</ref>

